<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<quiz>
  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Finding the height of a lighthouse using two-stage angle-of-depression reasoning</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>
A student stands on a deck near the top of a {@structure@} at the coast of {@coast@}. The student's eyes are <b>{@eye@} m</b> above the deck floor shown in the diagram. The student looks down at a {@item@} floating on the sea. The angle of depression to the {@item@} is <b>{@theta@}&deg;</b>. The horizontal distance from the base of the {@structure@} to the {@item@} is <b>{@d@} m</b>.
</p>

<p>
Find the total height of the {@structure@} above sea level.
</p>

<div style="margin:10px 0;">
<svg width="520" height="300" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">

  <!-- Sea level / ground -->
  <line x1="55" y1="225" x2="405" y2="225" stroke="black" stroke-width="2"/>

  <!-- Viewing platform vertical -->
  <line x1="95" y1="225" x2="95" y2="75" stroke="black" stroke-width="2"/>

  <!-- Deck floor -->
  <line x1="95" y1="140" x2="145" y2="140" stroke="black" stroke-width="2"/>

  <!-- Eye-above-deck segment -->
  <line x1="145" y1="140" x2="145" y2="115" stroke="black" stroke-width="1.5"/>

  <!-- Eye point -->
  <circle cx="145" cy="115" r="3" fill="black"/>

  <!-- Horizontal through eye -->
  <line x1="145" y1="115" x2="280" y2="115" stroke="black" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="6,4"/>

  <!-- Line of sight -->
  <line x1="145" y1="115" x2="330" y2="225" stroke="black" stroke-width="2"/>

  <!-- Right angle marker -->
  <path d="M95 210 L108 210 L108 225" fill="none" stroke="black" stroke-width="1.5"/>

  <!-- Angle arc -->
  <path d="M165 115 A22 22 0 0 1 158 131" fill="none" stroke="black" stroke-width="1.5"/>

  <!-- Labels near the top -->
  <text x="150" y="110" font-size="14">eye</text>
  <text x="118" y="128" font-size="15">{@eye@} m</text>
  <text x="170" y="129" font-size="15">{@theta@}°</text>

  <!-- Left-side label -->
  <text x="18" y="155" font-size="15">height = ?</text>

  <!-- Deck label -->
  <text x="120" y="156" font-size="13">deck</text>

  <!-- Bottom labels -->
  <text x="210" y="245" font-size="15">{@d@} m</text>
  <text x="316" y="244" font-size="14">{@item@}</text>
  <text x="336" y="214" font-size="13">sea level</text>

</svg>
</div>

<p>
Distance = [[input:ans1]] <b>m</b> [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]
</p>

<p>
Give your answer correct to <b>1 decimal place</b>.
</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
Step 1: Identify the right triangle.
</p>

<p>
The angle of depression is measured from the horizontal through the student's eye.
The horizontal distance is {@d@} m.
The unknown vertical drop from the eye to the sea is the opposite side.
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Use tangent.
</p>

<p>
\[
\tan({@theta@}^\circ)=\frac{\text{vertical drop}}{@d@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Let the vertical drop be \(x\).
Then
\[
x={@d@}\tan({@theta@}^\circ)
\]
</p>

<p>
\[
x \approx {@m1r@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Add the eye height above the deck.
</p>

<p>
The total height of the {@structure@} is:
</p>

<p>
\[
\text{height} = x + {@eye@}
\]
</p>

<p>
\[
\text{height} \approx {@m1r@} + {@eye@} = {@height1@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the total height of the {@structure@} above sea level is:
</p>

<p>
\[
\boxed{@height1@} \text{ m}
\]
</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
